modules.description: This module processes ocamldoc comments in OCaml source files to extract library configuration data, specifically scanning for `module _ = SomeLibrary_Name` expressions in both implementations (`.ml`) and interfaces (`.mli`). It provides functions to scan, merge, and query remote library specifications based on target ABI, enabling build systems to resolve and download dependencies embedded in source code comments. Key operations include scanning AST structures, merging configuration sets, and retrieving remote specs by library identifier.

This module defines data structures and operations for handling remote specifications in a build or deployment context. It supports types like `sec`, `cload`, `standard`, and `kind` to represent different remote configurations, including mirrors and library paths. Functions include parsing from ocamldoc comments, replacing ABI placeholders, and comparing or printing specifications.

Processes ocamldoc comments to extract and merge library configuration data, resolving remote dependencies based on target ABI. Works with AST structures and custom specification types to scan, query, and merge remote library metadata directly from source files. Enables build systems to automatically detect and download embedded dependencies by analyzing `module _ = SomeLibrary_Name` expressions in `.ml` and `.mli` files.
